creator: Plenti Australia
descriptionHtml:
Plenti investors make their money go further, faster through flexible investment options. Join over 20,000 investors already registered with Plenti.

· Earn attractive returns investing in consumer loans
· $10 minimum investment
· Flexible investment terms

When it comes to money, every decision counts. That’s why we’re on a mission to help everyone to make the right choices – about the choices that count. We’ve built a new world of lending that seeks to make investing faster and simpler for all.

* Investing is as simple as 1,2,3*
1. Register for an account online in 5 minutes
2. Download the app and login to your account
3. Transfer in funds and start investing in loans

WHY INVESTORS CHOOSE PLENTI

*Attractive asset class*
We give everyday Australians the opportunity to earn stable, attractive returns offered by investing in personal loans, car loans and green loans. Previously, only banks and institutions had access to the consumer credit asset class.

*Provision Fund protection*
The Provision Fund helps protect your returns. While it’s no guarantee, no investor has lost a cent of interest or principal as due.^

*Flexible investment options*
Choose to invest in lending markets with indicative terms from 1 month – 7 years.
As borrowers repay their loans, you’ll receive regular payments which you can choose to automatically reinvest.

READY TO GET STARTED?

Visit www.plenti.com.au/investing to find out more about investing with Plenti and register for an account. Signing up only takes five minutes.
Or email us at contact@plenti.com.au if you have any questions about investing.

IMPORTANT INFORMATION

As with every investment, investing with Plenti is not without risk.
Plenti RE Limited ABN 57 166 646 635 holds Australian financial services licence number 449176, Australian credit licence number 449176 and is a member of the Australian Financial Complaints Authority (AFCA).

This information should not be taken as financial product advice and has been prepared as general information only without consideration for your particular investment objectives, financial circumstances or particular needs. You should read the Product Disclosure Statement on www.plenti.com.au/pds before making any decision about your investment choices.

† ”Earn up to” rate represents the interest rate limit for the 5 Year Income lending market.
^ The Provision Fund is not a guarantee and your capital is at risk.

title: Plenti

creator: Plenti Australia
descriptionHtml:
Investing with Plenti



Plenti investors make their money go further, faster through flexible investment options. Join over 20,000 investors already registered with Plenti.

· Attractive returns investing in consumer loans
· $10 minimum investment
· Flexible investment terms

When it comes to money, every decision counts. That’s why our mission is to help everyone make the right choices when it counts. We’ve built a new world of lending to make investing faster and simpler for all.

Why investors choose Plenti

*Attractive asset class*
We give everyday Australians the opportunity to earn stable, attractive returns offered by investing in personal, car and green loans. Previously, only banks and institutions had access to the consumer credit asset class.

*Provision Fund protection*
The Provision Fund helps protect your returns. While it’s no guarantee, no investor has lost a cent of interest or principal as due.^

*Flexible investment options*
Invest in lending markets with indicative terms from 1 month – 7 years. As borrowers repay their loans, you’ll receive regular payments you can choose to automatically reinvest.

Ready to get started?

Visit www.plenti.com.au/investing to find out more about investing with Plenti and register for an account. Signing up only takes five minutes. Please email contact@plenti.com.au if you have questions.

*Important investor information*

As with every investment, investing with Plenti is not without risk.

Plenti RE Limited ACN 166 646 635 holds Australian Financial Services Licence number 449176, Australian Credit Licence number 449176 and is a member of the Australian Financial Complaints Authority.

This information should not be taken as financial product advice and has been prepared as general information only without consideration for your investment objectives, financial circumstances or particular needs. You should read the Product Disclosure Statement before making any decision about your investment choices.

^ The Provision Fund is not a guarantee and your capital is at risk.

Borrowing from Plenti



Plenti's loans range from $2,001 to $400,000 for terms of 6 months to 7 years.

Maximum annual percentage rate is 48%.

*Representative Example*: Based on an unsecured personal loan of $30,000 over 60 months a borrower with an excellent credit history can expect to pay a total of $35,126. This represents a comparison rate of 6.39% p.a#. and includes all interest and fees included in your loan repayments over the life of the loan. We are required to disclose the Target Market Determination (“TMD”) for each of our loan products. See our TMD documentation.

Comparison rate is correct as at 1/4/2022 and is subject to change.

*#Warning*: This comparison rate is true only for the examples given and may not include all fees and charges. Different terms, fees or other loan amounts might result in a different comparison rate. This estimate is not an offer, quote or approval of credit. The actual repayment amount and comparison rate will be confirmed if an application is submitted and approved. Finance provided to approved applicants only. All applications subject to credit assessment and eligibility criteria. Plenti's credit criteria, terms and conditions, fees and charges apply.

Credit provided by Finance Pty Limited ACN 636 759 861 (supported by its servicer, Plenti RE Limited ACN 166 646 635), Plenti RE Limited or Perpetual Corporate Trust Limited ACN 000 341 533 as custodian of the Plenti Lending Platform. Plenti RE Limited holds Australian Credit Licence 449176. Perpetual Corporate Trust Limited holds Australian Credit Licence 392673.

*Privacy*

By accessing and using our app, you agree to be bound by our Privacy Policy and Terms and Conditions.
